## 2026-03-07 - US-042
- `game/systems/npcApp..."
US-042 is complete.

**What was done:**
- `game/systems/npcAppearance.test.ts` already had 10 tests covering determinism, seed variation, valid base model, incompatibility rules, and role affinity вҖ” all passing
- Added the missing "all base models reachable" test: runs 500 seeds across all 6 roles and asserts every base model (basemesh, archer, knight, merchant, ninja, student) appears at least once
- Result: **11 tests**, all green; 1654 total tests, 0 failures; `tsc --noEmit` clean

`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`
- The "all base models reachable" test is a *coverage invariant*, not a correctness test вҖ” it guards against accidentally making a model unreachable via RNG weighting. The key is choosing N large enough (500) relative to the affinity skip probability (30%) that every model appears in the expected set.
- This story was mostly pre-satisfied because the mandatory Docs > Tests > Code workflow on US-041 already shipped tests for `npcAppearance.ts`. US-042 only needed the one reachability gap filled.
